# pxx.skip — FPC-testsuite conformance skip list (rung 1, feature-pascal-corpus-fpc-testsuite)
# One test per line: name.pp<TAB>reason. Burn down ticket by ticket; anything
# not passing, not auto-gated, and not listed here = FAIL.
# Baseline audit 2026-07-10: 222 pass / 294 skip-listed / 34 auto-gated (of 550 curated).
# Re-audit 2026-07-11 (headerless-program fix, suite re-fetched): 213 pass /
# 303 skip-listed / 34 auto-gated. The header fix green-lit 13 formerly
# failing tests and un-blocked 111 header-required skips (15 pass outright,
# rest re-listed with their real first error); it also EXPOSED 24 {%FAIL}
# negative tests that pxx now compiles instead of rejecting — those were
# previously "passing" only because the mandatory-header error rejected them
# for the wrong reason (see bug-pascal-missing-diagnostics-fail-tests).
# Re-audit 2026-07-11b (case-of-string lowering + case-label validation,
# bug-case-of-string-segfault-and-label-validation): 238 pass / 278
# skip-listed / 34 auto-gated. Burned the tcase cluster (21 entries incl. all
# exit=139 segfaults + the {%FAIL} label-validation tests); the 26 tcase
# sources, enum parsing, or the `otherwise` clause — not on case handling.
